NUMBER 3900
NAME Dark Keep
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
OUTDOOR_OTHER
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Like a blackened icon from a horrible nightmare, a dark keep juts oppressively
from the side of the mountains. Square in design, the keep's back wall is the
mountainside. It almost appears as if the keep grew to loom like a maleficent
harbinger of evil over Fayd and its environs. The keep is made of jet black
stone and here and there on the walls and towers are inset the skulls of
various humanoids in star-like patterns. The grins of the skulls mock life
and seem to whisper tales of death if one listens closely enough to the
mournful wind which swirls around the walls of the keep. A rotting bridge,
made of black wood, leads into the keep, while a weed-infested path cuts
into a dark copse of trees to the west. A narrow trail curves around the
side of the keep to the northeast, and the ever-present green mist leads
back towards the outside world. The moat surrounding the keep is filled
with a thick, bubbling, blackish liquid.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 3901
ITEM 0 1230 VAL2=567
ITEM 1 80 VAL2=3904
ITEM 2 608 VAL2=3911
ITEM 3 1231
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 3
Looking closer at the blackish liquid you discern that it is actually dark blood! Every few moments various pieces of humanoids bubble to the surface and then sink back down to the murky depths.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
The rotting bridge sways unsteadily in the wind. You can see what might be a fairly safe path across.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The mist is sickly green. Staring at it too long fills you with unease and horror.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB GO 2
	ECHO PLAYER Treading carefully across a safe portion of the bridge you manage to make it across, though you do have to make a small leap to safety at the end as a board gives way.
	ECHO OTHERS %N treads %h way carefully across the bridge, jumping into the keep at the last moment as a board creaks dangerously.
	AFFECT 3911
	ECHO OTHERS %N lands gracefully having just jumped off the bridge.
	AFFECT 3900
ENDIF
IFVERB GO 0
	ECHO PLAYER Nausea and horror bombard your senses as you cross through the sickly mist.
	AFFECT 567
	ECHO OTHERS %N arrives, looking slightly ill.
	AFFECT 3900
ENDIF
;
