NUMBER 3903
NAME Cave
FIXED_LIGHT
CAVE
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Pure white light flickers and dances along the smooth, marble walls of this rounded cavern. The light blinks from a large orb which is set upon a pedestal in the center of the cavern floor. Aside from the orb and pedestal the cavern holds no other items of interest.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 3902
ITEM 0 292
ITEM 1 1233 ADJ1=178
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The pedestal seemingly grows right out of the floor of the cavern, and is made of the same bluish marble as the rest of the room.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
The orb is made of a shimmering glassy material. Its interior is filled with a gauzy, white light which seeps out of the orb and casts itself over the walls of the cavern.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFENTRY
	IFVAR ALIGN > 0
		ECHO PLAYER The orb's light fills you with a feeling of goodness. You could swear that you hear a whispering in your mind, coming from the inside of the orb.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CONCENTRATE 1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER As you concentrate upon the orb you see images of a man, dressed in golden armor and wielding a sword flickering with the light of the sun, enter this chamber and approach the orb. After doing something to the orb the man disappears, and the images fade.
	ECHO OTHERS %N concentrates upon the orb, with a glassy look in %h eyes.
ENDIF
VARIABLE ORLIN
VARIABLE ORLIN1
IFSAY orlin
	ECHO ALL As the name is said the orb's light seems to grow stronger.
	ADD ORLIN 1
ENDIF
IFVERB TAP 1
	ADD ORLIN1 1
	IFVAR ORLIN => 1
		IFVAR ORLIN1 == 3
			ECHO ALL As %N taps the orb for the third time it slowly begins to descend into the floor. After a few moments it fully disappears and is replaced by a stairway spiraling down into the darkness.
			NEWITEM 2 81 VAL2=3944
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
	IFVAR ORLIN < 1
		EQUAL ORLIN1 0
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB CLIMB 2
	ECHO PLAYER The orb and pedestal appear to cover the stairway again as you descend.
	ECHO OTHERS The orb and pedestal rise to cover the stairway as %N descends.
	MOVE 3944
	REMOVEITEM 2
	EQUAL orlin 0
	EQUAL orlin1 0
ENDIF
