NUMBER 3905
NAME Orchard
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Nestled in a this small vale, with sheer mountain walls enclosing it on all sides but one, is an orchard. The orchard sits on a small hill and is composed of ordered rows of black and dead mirmach trees. Though dead, the trees still have leaves growing from their branches. An eerie wind blows down from the peaks of the Teeth of Shartan and whistles through the orchard, making the dead leaves rustle ominously. A small path leads up, back towards the keep.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 3906
EXIT U 3904
IFPREVERB SMELL -1
        ECHO PLAYER The sickly, sweet smell of something dead and rotting assaults your nostrils and brings bile to your throat.
        ECHO OTHERS A look of nausea passes over %N's face.
ENDIF
;
