NUMBER 3907
NAME Orchard
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The dead mirmarch trees are more spread apart in this section of the orchard.
The reason for the closely cropped trees to the south is now evident. Each of
the trees here have bodies hanging from thier branches like ripe fruit ready
to be plucked. There are five corpses to a tree in this most unholy of all
orchards which sway sickeningly in the wind, a single branch, imbedded in
their backs, the only thing holding them fastened to the trees. A sickening
smell of charnel is carried along on the mountain wind that blows through this
place. A path runs north and southwest along the rows of trees.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 3908
EXIT SW 3906
ITEM 0 232
ITEM 1 229
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The corpses are extremely pale and, judging by the fashion of the shredded clothing, have been hanging here a long time. Their internal organs must have long ago disappeared or been devoured, for the corpses are little more than skin and bones.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
The trees are uniform in that they are all mirmach trees, and in that they are all dead. Their leaves are still green in color, but have a crimson tint to them.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB TOUCH 1
        ECHO PLAYER The tree shudders slightly, almost as if it can sense your living essence. A moment later the leaves glow a bright red, and dark crimson blood begins to pool and drip off of the leaves.
        ECHO OTHERS %N's touch sends a shiver through the tree. A moment later a bright red glow plays over the leaves, and dark crimson blood begins to drip from them onto the ground of the orchard.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LISTEN 1
        ECHO PLAYER You can hear, barely, a soft murmur coming from the trees. The sound sends a chill up your spine as the words you can discern are evil ones of bloodlust and desire for life.
        ECHO OTHERS A look of disgust passes over %n's face.
ENDIF
NUMBER 3908
NAME Orchard
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The orchard comes to an end here as the rows of mirmach trees run up against
the sheer face of the mountains. The ever-present corpses hanging from the
trees swing slowly as you pass them by, their silent mouths still seemingly
imploring you to do something about their horrible condition. The corpses
closest to the mountain-side bump rhytmically against the rocks, scraping
their flesh raw and making the bodies drip blood onto the blackened ground.
The steady pounding of flesh meeting rock echoes throughout this section of
the orchard, only silenced when a strong wind blows through the vale.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 3907
ITEM 0 232
ITEM 1 229
IFVERB LISTEN -1
        ECHO PLAYER The rhythmic thudding of flesh against stone grows louder and louder in your ears as you stand here, driving out all other sounds.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3909
NAME Orchard, giant tree
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Just about in the center of the orchard sits a gigantic mirmach tree which
towers above those surrounding it. Like the other trees in this foul orchard,
the giant tree has bodies attached to its branches, but the bodies on this
tree match its size. Three giants hang from the black branches of the evil
tree, their corpses long since sucked dry of everything internal, leaving only
lifeless husks of skin and bone. This tree seems almost alive, for it shivers
slightly when it senses your life essence within its reach. The large crimson
tinted leaves of the tree continuously drip blood onto the ground. The ground
seems almost thirsty as it sucks up the blood, leaving only a dark spot where
it falls.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 3906
ITEM 0 232 ADJ1=142
ITEM 1 72 VAL2=3910
ITEM 2 229 ADJ1=142
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The giants, from what you can tell from their emaciated condition, seem to be closely related to those giants now found within the demense of the Teeth of Shartan; the only distinguishing characteristic being that these giants are a bit smaller. Their tattered clothing seems to suggest a mode of dress that akin to the way that other intelligent humanoids clothe themselves.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB RECALL -1
        IFVAR SKILL32 = 1
                ECHO PLAYER You realize that the three giants seem very familiar to you.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR SKILL32 => 2
                IFVAR SKILL32 =< 4
                        ECHO PLAYER You remember a story that you came across in your studies of Fayd's history, about three giant brothers who were prominent citizens about the time of Malthesia's coming.
                ENDIF
        ENDIF
        IFVAR SKILL32 => 5
                ECHO PLAYER With startling clarity you remember that these three giants, Gylvin, Berantik, and Wiltnich, were three prominent citizens of Fayd during the era of Malthesia. The three brothers had founded a successful construction company, and were respected as good and lawful friends of all of Fayd. History never recorded what happened to them, except for a small footnote concerning some new building project in the mountains.
        ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB SEARCH -1
        ECHO PLAYER You spy a small opening at the base of the tree!
ENDIF
