NUMBER 3910
NAME Under Orchard
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
INDOOR_FLOOR
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This large earthen chamber is filled with the dust and cobwebs of many
centuries. A dim red glow comes from the center of the chamber, its source
a circular pool filled with blood! Hanging above the pool, and dripping blood
into it, are numerous tree roots. The roots angle into the room from the
earthen walls and ceiling. Looking closely at the roots you realize that
they fairly throb as they continously drip blood drained from their victims
above. The iron-rich odor of the blood overwhelms all other
smells within the chamber.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 3909
ITEM 0 324
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The pool seems to be continously draining itself so as to not overflow from the supply of blood that it continously receives. Where the blood is draining to is a mystery not solved here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB SMELL -1
        ECHO PLAYER The overpowering smell of the rich blood makes you gag as you take a deep breath.
        ECHO OTHERS %N takes a deep breath and then begins gagging.
ENDIF
