INDOOR_FLOOR
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Long tables and shelves filled with instruments of torture and mutilation
suggest that this room was where Malthesia conducted his necromantic
experiments. Many of the tables have skeletons strapped to them, lying
undisturbed throughout the many centuries. In certain spots of the room
appear to be signs of a struggle. A single door sits in the center of the
northern wall. It is unapproachable though, for a blue light covers the
entire door and impedes any progress whatsoever. Looking about the room,
the only other item of interest is a cylindrical beam of red
light in the southeastern corner.
*DESCRIPTION_END
