*DESCRIPTION_START
The darkness swirls around this hallway like a heavy mist, clinging to the walls and floor. Every surface is slick to the touch, a slight sheen of water covering the rough-hewn granite. Inky blackness hangs overhead obscuring any view of the ceiling. The tunnel runs towards the west where you can see a faint glow. A corpse sprawls across one corner a few feet in front of the archway leading out. Shrouded in darkness, the corpse is impossible to view without leaning closer.
*DESCRIPTION_END
