*DESCRIPTION_START
Swirling colors dance across the polished black walls of this large,
cathedral-like room. The source of the display are hideous stone heads
set into the four opposing walls of the chamber. One color is emitted
from the eyes of each head, all joining together in a pattern is somehow
disturbing in the way it plays across the room. Four carved archways,
each one covered with representations of different demons, lead in
different directions from the room. Sitting on the mosaic that covers
the entire floor is an altar of black obsidian.
*DESCRIPTION_END
