 ECHO PLAYER You feel a slight tingling course through your body as you enter the opening.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3992
NAME Under Keep, hallway
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A thick coat of black ice covers the entirety of this hallway, making the footing treacherous and uneven. Sharp, jagged icicles hang from the walls and ceiling, whilst some can be seen protruding from the floor. The dried blood present upon a few icy points gives testimony that this portion of the hallway is not for the unwary. The light comes from a few of the icy stalagmites that glow with a deep red hue. The hallway continues on its frozen trail to the northeast and southwest.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 3993
EXIT SW 3991
ITEM 0 420
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The flickering crimson light casts an eerie glow upon the walls, nearly making you miss what is contained within the ice...the lifeless, frozen bodies of youngters from all the races of Andor are trapped within the immovable ice. Their little bodies are twisted and shattered, as if they had been forced into these grotesque positions before being encased....
*DESCRIPTION_END
CALL 24
MONSTER_GROUP 81
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER You strain your hearing to the limit and faintly, very faintly...you think that you hear the sound of something scraping, slowly, against the ice...
  ECHO OTHERS %N leans close to the icy wall, listening intently.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3993
NAME Under Keep, frozen hallway
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The ice, clinging heavily to the stone of the passage becomes thicker here. The ice cracks and shatters in spots as it is stepped upon, sending booming noises echoing up and down the long corridor. The sparse light in the corridor barely outlines vague forms in the passage walls. The forms, bodies perhaps, seem to move with the light, as if being drawn towards its heat.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT SW 3992
EXIT N 3994
ITEM 0 420
CALL 24
MONSTER_GROUP 81
IFPREVERB LIGHT 0
  CLEARVERB
   ADD flag1 1
    IFVAR flag1 = 1
     ECHO PLAYER You move your light source closer to the frozen wall...the frozen forms, is it a trick of the light or your eyes?, seem to be drawn towards the flame...almost as if they hunger....
     ECHO OTHERS %N moves %h light source closer to the frozen wall..staring at its surface with terrible fascination.
     EQUAL ROUNDTIME 15
    ENDIF
     IFVAR flag1 = 2
       ECHO PLAYER You hold the light source closer...water begins to bead on the frozen surface of the wall...and...is that a faint moaning coming from within the wall? A spine-tingling sound that brings visions of your darkest nightmares dancing in your head...
       ECHO OTHERS %N gasps in horror as %s holds %h light source closer to the wall...
       EQUAL ROUNDTIME 20
     ENDIF
      IFVAR flag1 = 3
       ECHO PLAYER You feel compelled by some strange force to keep the heat upon the wall...the water begins to flow freely down the wall in small streams, the ice begins to heave and crack...then...in an explosion of icy shards a shadowy form leaps from the wall and wraps its arms around you...!
       POSITION LAY
       ECHO PLAYER You smell the fetid breath of the corpse washing over your face as it whispers in your ear...
       ECHO PLAYER The tongue of the rotting corpse flicks over your ear as it whispers, "Enianak untona yalonth varunaman a' ohqer pielnak berthnai a' klomak!", to you. The corpse tries to cling to you... but, then, you sense a powerful presence that is binding the corpse, pulling it back... back into the wall, to be once again covered with the sheet of ice!
       ECHO OTHERS %N slowly presses the flame closer to the wall, eyes entranced by the streams of water flowing down it...with a sharp cracking noise the sheet of ice explodes outward, showering you with small shards of ice! A black, rotting corpse falls from the wall, onto %N and clings to %i in a horrible embrace. %N falls to the floor, screaming in terror, as the corpse holds fast to %i...then, almost as suddenly as it began to corpse seems to flow back into the wall, covered again by a sheet of ice.
       EQUAL ROUNDTIME 15
    ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
 IFVAR flag1 => 3
  IFVAR SKILL32 < 5
   ECHO PLAYER The strange words whispered to you by the corpse tickle your mind... you know that it is from an ancient, dead language... but, are not quite sure of their meaning.
   ECHO PLAYER As you ponder the ancient words... you feel them flow from your mind.
   EQUAL FLAG1 0
  ENDIF
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 6
    IFVAR SKILL32 < 10
     ECHO PLAYER The strange words whispered to you by the corpse tickle your mind... you know that it is from an ancient, dead language..but, are not quite sure of their meaning. The language is one that primiraly used by scholars and mages, but it died out many years ago, and you don't think anyone uses it anymore.
     ECHO PLAYER As you ponder the ancient words...you feel them flow from your mind.
     EQUAL FLAG1 0
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
    IFVAR SKILL32 > 10
     ECHO PLAYER The strange words whispered to you by the corpse tickle your mind... you know that it is from an ancient, dead language..but, are not quite sure of their meaning. The language is one that primiraly used by scholars and mages, but it died out many years ago, and you don't think anyone uses it anymore.
     ECHO PLAYER You, however, have studied this ancient language extensively, and know that the phrase translates to...
     ECHO PLAYER "Emeralds glow with a crimson hue as they flash across a sky of darkness."
     ECHO PLAYER As you ponder the ancient words... you feel them flow from your mind...
     EQUAL FLAG1 0
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
