NUMBER 3995
NAME Under Keep, ice sculptures
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Cold tendrils of a wispy mist flow around numerous sculptures that are randomly placed in this wide corridor. Swirling on the mist are black snowflakes, a few of them gently descending only to disappear in a burst of intense flame as they touch the icy floor of the passage. The sculptures have all been formed from the same black ice that clings to the walls and ceiling of the corridor, and they all seem strangely familiar.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NW 3991
EXIT SW 3996
ITEM 0 481 ADJ1=165
EXTEND 0 of Rarg Windrunner
ITEM 1 481 ADJ1=165
EXTEND 1 of Strom O'Berin
ITEM 2 481 ADJ1=165
EXTEND 2 of Orlin Thinvar
ITEM 3 481 ADJ1=165
EXTEND 3 of Tilvaen Treegrower
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The sculpture of Rarg portrays him standing in the middle of roaring flames, a sneer set upon his young face as he feeds the fire around him with a struggling young child.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
The sculpture of Strom portrays him kneeling over the body of a wounded warrior, his arms extended towards the sky, yet receiving no aid as the warrior in front of him slowly dies, in great agony....
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
The sculpture of Orlin portrays him cowering before the majestic figure of Malthesia. Sunstrike lies discarded to one side of Orlin, and his pose seems to suggest a pathetic plea for mercy....
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 3
Tilvaen stands in the center of a group of five disease ridden children, a look of horror upon his face as he gazes at the dead child he has just given some potion to, from the small cask he holds...
*DESCRIPTION_END
CALL 24
MONSTER_GROUP 81
IFENTRY
  RANDOM dummy2 1 100 0
  ADD dummy2 AGI
   IFVAR dummy2 =< 135
    ECHO PLAYER You fall on the slick floor and bump your head. It takes you a few seconds to recover your senses...
    ECHO OTHERS %N falls on the slick floor and bumps %h head. %S seems kind of dazed as %s lays on the floor.
    DAMAGE CRUSH 5 %N seems slightly dazed from the fall.
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 10
    ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You nearly lose your footing on the slick floor, but agilely remain in an upright position.
    ECHO OTHERs %N nearly loses %h footing on the slick floor, but agilely remains in an upright position.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3996
NAME Under Keep, statue
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Flowing, seamlessly, from the ice-covered stone floor is the statue of a beautiful young woman. The statue seems out of place in these surroundings, its beauty a stark contrast to the bleakness of the ice-covered stone passageway. A chill breeze flows through this area, following the corridor as it curves to the northeast and west.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 3995
EXIT W 3998
ITEM 0 346
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The young woman is extremely beautiful, her features captured in the prime of her life and memorialized forever. Her eyes are open and her lips are tilted in a gentle smile that seems to follow you wherever you go in this small portion of the passage. Something tugs at your mind as you gaze at the statue....somehow it bears a striking resemblance to someone very familiar. At the base of the statue are what seem to be a few drops of dried blood...
*DESCRIPTION_END
CALL 24
MONSTER_GROUP 81
VARIABLE statblo
IFENTRY
 IFVAR statblo = 5
  ECHO PLAYER The statue radiates heat, looking almost life-like as its lips part in a slight smile.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB SEARCH -1
  ECHO PLAYER You spot a trail of blood, running from the base of the statue and growing large as it goes towards the west...
ENDIF
IFSAY hello?
 IFVAR statblo = 5
  IFVAR INTNUM43 => 50
   ECHO PLAYER The statue smiles gently at you, leaning forward to whisper, almost seductively, "My greetings to you, gentle being."
   ECHO OTHERS The statue smiles gently at %N and then whispers something to %i.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY malthesia?
 IFVAR statblo = 5
  IFVAR INTNUM43 => 50
   ECHO PLAYER The statue sighs and looks away, its eyes closing, "My husband...Do not ask for more, I will not speak of it..."
   ECHO OTHERS The statue sighs and looks away, then whispers something to %N.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
