NUMBER 3997
NAME Under Keep, blood trail
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A cold breeze from the southwest swirls through this small chamber tossing the hay strewn here into small eddies around the room. Currenlt empty shackles and chains hang loosely from the wall at intervals. Bloody handprints mark the left wall, getting lower and lower as they travel towards the southeast, until finally the handprints begin to appear in long streaks, as if someone was dragging, him, or herself along the wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT SE 3998
EXIT NE 3991
CALL 24
MONSTER_GROUP 81
IFVERB SMELL -1
 IFVAR RAC = 4
  ECHO PLAYER Your sensitive nostrils bring you the scent of cubs in fear... it is nearly overpowering....
  ECHO OTHERS %N growls angrily as %s sniffs the air.
  ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You detect the scent of some animal on the breeze.
  ECHO OTHERS %N sniffs the air and looks around questioningly.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3998
NAME Under Keep, blood
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Congealed pools of blood, with pieces of flesh floating in them, sit stagnantly along the floor of this passage. Smeared streaks of blood can be seen along the northern wall, flowing downwards until they reach a body that lies slumped against the icy wall. Most of the blood in this room seems to have come from this body, and runs in little streams to other locations.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NW 3997
EXIT E 3996
ITEM 0 1696
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
Perfectly preserved, due the intense cold, is the body of a young human male. His eyes stare, unseeing, up at the ceiling above him. Blood has frozen on the lips of his open mouth, open, and frozen, in a scream of terror. Your eyes travel down his body, to his chest which has been torn open by some powerful force. Peering into the chest cavity you notice that the body's heart is missing.
*DESCRIPTION_END
CALL 24
MONSTER_GROUP 81
VARIABLE rotcor
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER A slight breeze assaults your nose with the scent of rotting flesh, intermingled with the sickly-sweet scent of blood.
  ECHO OTHERS %N gulps, %h gorge rising.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB2 PUT 0
  CLEARVERB
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 1697
     REMOVEITEM -1
      ECHO PLAYER Clenching your teeth, to keep the bile from rising, you carefully position the heart inside the chest cavity of the young man....
      ECHO OTHERS %N clenches %h teeth and carefully places the heart within the chest cavity of the body....
      ECHO ALL %c%c%c
      ECHO ALL The eyelids of the body flicker...and a low, keening moan escapes its lips...%c>%cThe body turns its head, with the sound of cartilage breaking, and looks at %N....%c>%cWith a rasping sound the body speaks, "The Starwings sing to protect her. I loved her...." then stops...
      SETEVENT 71 3 ALWAYS
      CONTEVENT 71
      ECHO ALL Suddenly the body continues, "He put me down here, a great joke, no?"%c>%cThe corpse laughs, sending shivers down your spine at the sound. The corpse says, "I knew I would die, but I would have gotten my revenge, I had learned how."%c>%cThe corpse closes its eyes and leans back, as if reflecting...
      ECHO ALL %cThe eyelids flash open quickly, staring intently at %N, "Two rare items, from their minions bodies, to be consumed by the white altar, "Heed my call, I summon thee forth," then you must use the abominations true name, "By the name,    , I destroy thee!"", the body then slumps over, lifeless.
      ADD rotcor 1
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
 IFVAR rotcor => 1
  IFVAR SKILL32 = 1
   ECHO PLAYER You remember coming across a story about two young scholars who disappearead a long time ago.
  ENDIF
   IFVAR SKILL32 = 2
    ECHO PLAYER You remember coming across a story about two young scholars who disappearead a long time ago.
    ECHO PLAYER The two young scholars were fascinated by Malthesia, it seems and were last heard discussing a visit to his Keep.
   ENDIF
    IFVAR SKILL32 => 3
     ECHO PLAYER You remember coming across a story about two young scholars who disappearead a long time ago.
     ECHO PLAYER The two young scholars were fascinated by Malthesia, it seems and were last heard discussing a visit to his Keep.
     ECHO PLAYER They supposedly lived in Fayd around the year 540 and their names were Tarben and Sailena.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
