ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The three ice walls enclosing the northern end of this corridor pulsate in a rhythmic pattern. Each outward buckling of the walls is accompanied by a shrill scream that resonates painfully within your ears, only to be eased as the walls draw inward with an accompanying sigh of relief. A chest, made of black ice and inset with the frozen eyeballs of humans, is fastened to the floor at the northen end of this corridor.
*DESCRIPTION_END
