    EQUAL ruby5 1
    ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER The lever is already in a fixed position.
    ECHO OTHERS %N attempts to pull the lever, to no avail.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1044
NAME Under Keep, music room
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The polished black marble walls and floors of this massive chamber are streaked through with blood red streaks giving it a macabre effect that is only enhanced by the large organ placed against the southern wall. The organ takes up the entire wall and rests atop four human skeletons that are in a kneeling position. The framework of the organ consists mainly of blackened oak, but the other parts of it make you gasp in horror.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 60 VAL2=1043
ITEM 1 1701 ADJ1=178
ITEM 2 352 ADJ1=1
ITEM 3 352 ADJ1=100
ITEM 4 352 ADJ1=160
ITEM 5 352 ADJ1=353
ITEM 6 352 ADJ1=205
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Instead of the usual metal tubes through which the music of the organ travels there are five bodies. Each one rigidly held in place by glowing metal bands. The eyes of the bodies seem to beseech you for release, their pain seemingly unbearable. Your eyes are drawn to the keyboard..which consists of five skulls with glowing red eyes.
*DESCRIPTION_END
VARIABLE organ
VARIABLE organ1
VARIABLE organ2
IFVERB PUSH 5
  CLEARVERB
  EQUAL organ1 0
    IFVAR organ = 0
     ECHO ALL The wolfling, bound high up on the organ, seems to sigh with relief as what appears to be a soothing white light covers him.
     EQUAL organ 1
     EQUAL organ1 1
    ENDIF
     IFVAR organ ! 0
      IFVAR organ1 ! 1
       ECHO ALL The wolfling body screeches in pain as the bands holding him burn brightly. The noise pierces your hearing, causing extreme pain!
       SPELL 312
       EQUAL organ 0
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB PUSH 2
  CLEARVERB
  EQUAL organ1 0
    IFVAR organ = 1
     ECHO ALL The beautiful aelfen female, bound high up on the organ, seems to sigh with relief as what appears to be a soothing white light covers her.
     EQUAL organ 2
     EQUAL organ1 1
    ENDIF
     IFVAR organ ! 1
      IFVAR organ1 ! 1
       ECHO ALL The aelfen body screeches in pain as the bands holding her burn brightly. The noise pierces your hearing, causing extreme pain!
       SPELL 312
       EQUAL organ 0
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB PUSH 6
  CLEARVERB
  EQUAL organ1 0
    IFVAR organ = 2
     ECHO ALL The little murg, bound high up on the organ, seems to sigh with relief as what appears to be a soothing white light covers him.
     EQUAL organ 3
     EQUAL organ1 1
    ENDIF
     IFVAR organ ! 2
      IFVAR organ1 ! 1
       ECHO ALL The murg body screeches in pain as the bands holding him burn brightly. The noise pierces your hearing, causing extreme pain!
       SPELL 312
       EQUAL organ 0
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB PUSH 3
  CLEARVERB
  EQUAL organ1 0
    IFVAR organ = 3
     ECHO ALL The proud drakin, bound high up on the organ, seems to sigh with relief as what appears to be a soothing white light covers him.
     EQUAL organ 4
     EQUAL organ1 1
    ENDIF
     IFVAR organ ! 3
      IFVAR organ1 ! 1
       ECHO ALL The drakin body screeches in pain as the bands holding him burn brightly. The noise pierces your hearing, causing extreme pain!
       SPELL 312
       EQUAL organ 0
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB PUSH 4
  CLEARVERB
  EQUAL organ1 0
   IFVAR organ2 ! 5
    IFVAR organ = 4
     ECHO ALL The stout highlander, bound high up on the organ, seems to sigh with relief as what appears to be a soothing white light covers him.
     ECHO ALL You sense that something good has been accomplished, by easing some of the eternal suffering that these five souls are forced to endure.
     AFFECT 3991
     ECHO ALL The black altar is infused with a peaceful glow that, when it fades, changes the color of the altar to white!
     NEWITEM 5 236 ADJ1=247
     REMOVEITEM 0
     AFFECT 1044
     EQUAL organ 5
     EQUAL organ1 1
     EQUAL organ2 5
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
    IFVAR organ2 = 5
     IFVAR organ = 4
      ECHO ALL The stout highlander mouths words, that you barely pick up, "You have already eased our suffering for the day, thank you."
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
     IFVAR organ ! 4
      IFVAR organ1 ! 1
       ECHO ALL The wolfling body screeches in pain as the bands holding him burn brightly. The noise pierces your hearing, causing extreme pain!
       SPELL 312
       EQUAL organ 0
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
  IFVAR SKILL32 < 5
   ECHO PLAYER You have vague memories of reading something about spies, one from each race, who tried to infiltrate Malthesia's Keep many years ago.
  ENDIF
   IFVAR SKILL32 => 5
    ECHO PLAYER You have vague memories of reading something about spies, one from each race, who tried to infiltrate Malthesia's Keep many years ago.
    PLREVENT 1
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER As you ponder it further you remember how back in the early 400's, five people, Eroana Talstar, a beautiful aelfen mage, N'tak Korthan, a wise drakin scholar, Artyn Morningsun, a wolfling forester, Mokir Rockfoot, a fiercesome murg warrior, and Pakwur Ironheart, a colonel in Fayd's Intelligence Corps, tried to infiltrate Malthesia's defenses, to spy upon the newly completed Keep... they were never heard from again...
  ENDIF
ENDIF
